Task 3 – Coding & Collaboration Platforms

Part A – Coding Practice (HackerRank)

Platform Used  
HackerRank (hackerrank.com)

Work I Did  
I created an account on HackerRank and solved a beginner-level coding challenge. I have added a screenshot of the completed problem in this folder as proof of my work.

What I Learned  
Using HackerRank helped me understand how online coding platforms work. It automatically checks the code and provides instant feedback, which makes it easier to learn from mistakes and improve. It also gave me a basic idea of how coding tests are conducted.


Part B - Google Workspace Collaboration

What I Built  
I created a Google Form titled “Digital Literacy Awareness Quiz” with 5 questions for my batchmates. The form includes both multiple choice and short answer questions. I also linked the responses to a Google Sheet, which makes it easy to view and manage the data.

How These Tools Help Academically  
These tools will be very helpful during my B.Tech journey. HackerRank will allow me to practice coding regularly and gradually improve my problem-solving skills. Google Forms and Sheets will help me in collecting information, conducting surveys, and managing data efficiently, especially during group projects. Overall, these platforms support both my technical learning and collaboration skills.


